cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with human action recognition in videos. The use of non-linear path signature techniques also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of datasets and experimental results suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of a fully-connected network for classification suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
